the rude people I encounter on the streets.I have witnessed people ganging-up together with governments based on the “common-evil” practice of islam.

As a student in Tripoli, I have found a way of avoiding this issue by not mixing-up with too many Libyans…

1.Wrap yourself up in prayer-book-packaging.Clothe yourself top to bottom with the thinest lebntahs that covers all parts of your body other than your eyes and hands…Whites mixed with the right top and even a piece of veil covering your nose and up to your forehead will make people judge you as a believer more than those with golden bangles are not when spotted on the street…

2. March with pride along your way and never shy or bow down to some1..Tell them “Are you sattisfied with your life?”which most will not get and as such this will give me time to check them out and move on with the slowest one of them. They will follow you at thieir knocked knees

3. If in a bus with those who are nosy just use your hand and draw an invisible or imaginary animal/humman that eats people on one of their faces and you will find them sitting with their heads down not bothering to check you out again…Result: the company of curious/ nosy people to avoid travel.

4. Dress…people in Libya do not “dress” like they used-to this led to the dishonor
